I’ve settled on a deterministic repair path: discover existing `n00d/WETH` V2-style pairs on-chain, pick a profitable ordered pair if one exists at the fork block, flashswap `n00d`, run the same ERC777-recipient reentrancy against the local vault inside the callback, then unwind through the richer pool and repay in `WETH`. I’m patching the verifier now.
